35. per sacrum olivum; see on Epod. 7. 7 ‘ Britannus . . descend- eret sacra catenatus via.' Cp. Mart. 1. 71. 5. The name was given to the slope by which the ‘sacra via' descended, from the spot where its pavement is still visible under the Arch os Titus, into the Forum, a fall of 53 feet.
